article.headline: South Florida 77, Stetson 72 (2 OT)
article.story: TAMPA, Fla. (AP) -- Solomon Bozeman hit three free throws in the final nine seconds to seal a 77-72 victory in double overtime for South Florida over Stetson Monday. Stetson (2-4) had a chance to win in regulation, but Gabe McMillen missed a jumper from the free-throw line as time expired to leave the teams tied at 59. Melvin Buckley, who matched career-highs with 29 points and a dozen rebounds for South Florida, missed a last-second 3-pointer in the first overtime. McHugh Mattis scored 20 points and blocked seven shots for the Bulls (4-0). Bozeman finished with 17 points, five assists and three steals. Garfield Blair and Kris Thomas each had 18 points and Collins Okafor added 10 for the Hatters. Melvyn Richardson scored his only field goal of the night eight minutes into the second half to put South Florida ahead 43-36. Stetson responded with 14 unanswered points from six players to go ahead by seven. Buckley had 11 points midway through the first half to help the Bulls build an eight-point advantage. Mark Lohuis gave the Hatters a 29-27 lead on a put-back a minute before the break, but Bozeman hit a pair of free throws with three seconds left to tie it.
